  const file = files[0];
  const reader = new FileReader();

  reader.onload = (e) => {
    try {
      const result = parseLogFile(e.target.result);  // ← Calls parser
      loadEntries(result.entries, file.name, file.size, result.truncated);
    } catch (err) {
      alert(`Error parsing file: ${err.message}`);
    }
  };

  reader.readAsText(file);  // ← Reads as text
}
```

**State Management:**
- Stores file metadata: `fileName`, `fileSize`, `truncated` flag
- Maintains entries array and truncated status in application state
- Displays "Truncated" badge when truncation is detected

